MORNING commuters faced delays after signalling problems caused chaos across a number of train services.&nbsp;Trains from Milngavie to Cumbernauld, v&Atilde;&shy;a Motherwell, and those going from Dalmuir and Motherwell via Whifflet were delayed from 9am.Signalling problems are understood to have happened earlier in the morning on the Whifflet line.The Milngavie to Whifflet service is also affected by the signalling issues, with disruption expected to last until 10am according to operators Scotrail.The signalling problems have now been resolved and services are returning to normal.A ScotRail spokeswoman said: “We apologise to our customers for any inconvenience caused by signalling issues this morning.”